---

AGENT 1 — INTENT ANALYZER

Purpose: Convert vague user requests into:

concepts

domains

architectural areas

likely file categories



---

Example

Input:

Add retry support to failed webhooks

Output:

{
  "concepts": [
    "webhook",
    "retry",
    "queue",
    "failure"
  ],
  "architectural_areas": [
    "api",
    "worker",
    "scheduler",
    "config",
    "tests"
  ],
  "expected_patterns": [
    "retry policy",
    "backoff",
    "dead letter queue"
  ]
}

This seeds retrieval.


---

AGENT 2 — SCOUT AGENT

Purpose: Initial broad repo discovery.

ONLY allowed to:

search

inspect

summarize


NEVER allowed to:

plan

patch

modify


This separation is CRITICAL.


---

SCOUT STRATEGY

The scout should:

1. search keywords


2. inspect top files


3. extract:

imports

exports

symbols

nearby modules



4. recursively search those



This mimics how humans explore repos.


---

VERY IMPORTANT

Every inspected file should produce:

{
  "file": "webhookWorker.ts",
  "summary": "Processes webhook deliveries",
  "symbols": [
    "processWebhook",
    "retryDelivery"
  ],
  "imports": [
    "queue.ts"
  ],
  "confidence": 0.87,
  "reason": "Core delivery pipeline"
}

This is basically your:

lightweight repo map

Aider uses a similar idea with repo maps. 


---

AGENT 3 — EXPANSION AGENT (MOST IMPORTANT)

This is the BIGGEST missing piece in most no-code agents.

Your current observer likely:

finds initial files

stops too early


Instead:

recursively expand.


---

Expansion Logic

For EVERY discovered file:

inspect imports

inspect callers

inspect sibling files

inspect tests

inspect configs

inspect types


Then recursively repeat.


---

Example

Initial retrieval:

webhook.ts

Expansion:

queue.ts
retryPolicy.ts
webhook.test.ts
env.ts
worker.ts
types.ts

Then: expand AGAIN.

This is exactly what RepoMaster research emphasizes:

dependency graphs

hierarchical traversal

progressive exploration 



---

THE CRITICAL LOOP

You NEED this.

while retrieval_not_stable:
    search()
    inspect()
    expand_neighbors()
    identify_missing()
    merge_results()

THIS LOOP is the core intelligence.

Not prompting.


---

AGENT 4 — MISSING FILE CRITIC

This is EXTREMELY important.

After every retrieval cycle:

Ask:

Assume critical files are missing.
Which ones?

Force checks for:

tests

middleware

configs

types

validators

schemas

env files

migrations


This dramatically improves recall.


